{"type":"rich_text_quote","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Regarding app hangs: We appreciate Xcode 14's new runtime warnings around possible app hangs/UI unresponsiveness such as this one from `CoreLocation`s `CLLocationManager.locationServicesEnabled()`:

> This method can cause UI unresponsiveness if invoked on the main thread. Instead, consider waiting for the `-locationManagerDidChangeAuthorization:` callback and checking `authorizationStatus` first.

We're also observing app hangs from `HKHealthStore`'s `-authorizationStatusForType:`, however, Xcode does not produce any runtime warnings for them specifically. Is it known/expected that `-authorizationStatusForType:` may lead to UI unresponsiveness and if so, what are possible workarounds?"}]}

slackdump_thread_replies.text:
&gt; Hi there,
&gt; that's great feedback! As you noticed, Xcode 14 shows new runtime warnings about some API misuse. For now, many of these are special-cased warnings about commonly misused APIs, but we haven't audited all API yet.
&gt; 
&gt; We don't have a HealthKit engineer with us right now, so I can't answer whether `authorizationStatusForType` from `HKHealthStore` should be safe to run in terms of hangs or there is an async alternative to use instead. But it would be great to have this information.
&gt; 
&gt; If you see hangs being caused by `authorizationStatusForType` can you please file a feedback via <http://feedbackassistant.apple.com|feedbackassistant.apple.com> to ask for either the hang to be fixed or a runtime warning to be produced for API misuse?
&gt; 
&gt; If you feel the documentation isn't clear on how to use it, that's also great feedback to report!

